{"questionId":"9257","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows triangle ABC, with <em>AB</em> = 6 and <em>AC</em> = 8.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7840b884a17d4284b6b6a3cfe107725e64d1d612.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,\\hat A = \\frac{5}{6}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>A</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> find the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{sin}}\\,\\hat A\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>A</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach using Pythagorean identity&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\,A + {\\left( {\\frac{5}{6}} \\right)^2} = 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>si</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n            <mn>6</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{sin}}\\,A = \\frac{{\\sqrt {11} }}{6}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>11</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9257","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.1a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that cos A ^ = 5 6 find the value of sin A ^ .","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Pythagorean identity, double angles"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}